contact_name: Eurostat, the statistical office of the European Union
description: Percentage of persons in the labour force who have a nationality other than that of the country of residence. The labour force comprises all resident persons aged 15-64 that are either employed or unemployed but excludes inactive persons . This indicator provides three breakdowns: "Total" includes citizens of other EU countries and citizens of countries outside the EU; "Extra-EU" means citizens of countries outside the EU, and "Intra-EU" relates to citizens of other EU countries
title: Non-nationals in the labour force
